a.k.a. Cee Murda of the Faydark</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufreonsmurf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FreonSmurf</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC= http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif  BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/11/00 2:00:39 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://hoels76.tripod.com/wee.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PVP Advice</span><hr size=1> To the orignal poster:<br>
At this level, your best bet is to attack as many blue and green casters as possible.  If you see or are in a situation where there are red and yellow casters around you, just hide and scope things out.<br>
<br>
If ya read bluuds guide, ya will see his point about staying on top of casters in battle.  You gotta beat on them every second, so if you get rooted/snared/darkness you must pull out some shurikens or a bow and used that to innterupt thier casting.<br>
<br>
Get used to fighting all casters, know what to expect.<br>
When fighting a druid, what is the first spell he will cast?<br>
A dmg shield on himself or a snare on you.<br>
When fighting a mage, what is the best way to get rid of his pet?<br>
THere are some possible tricks to make the pet 32k, but thats kinda cheap.  Best thing to do is attack the pet with a range weapon.  Then run off somewhere in a dark corner.  Beat the @#%$ out of the pet.<br>
Then go back kill the casters.<br>
Why am I getting rooted or snared all the time?<br>
Rogue's are very dependant on equipment.  Know what kind you should have and save up for it. <p><P><center><font face ="Verdana,Arial" size="3" color="red">
